description: a very small pterosaur with a wingspan of only 1 foot. It had a very short tail and probably caught insects in mid-air.

The Dinosaur with a Secret Identity! Say hello to one of the biggest animals to ever walk the Earth! The plant-eating Apatosaurus was a truly massive dinosaur, easily reaching 70 feet long. Its name, which means Deceptive Lizard, is one of the coolest in science because it tells an amazing story. Over a century ago, during the famous Bone Wars of the late 1800s, two famous fossil hunters thought they had discovered two different dinosaurs: Apatosaurus and Brontosaurus. They were both huge, long-necked beasts! Soon, scientists decided these two names belonged to just one dino. Apatosaurus was the official winner, and Brontosaurus vanished! But hold on—the mystery isn't over! In a thrilling modern twist, new research has convinced many paleontologists that Brontosaurus was a real, unique dinosaur all along! It’s a scientific comeback story! This long-running debate is proof that even in science, there are still exciting legends waiting to be revived.
etymology: (Greek: apatos 'deceptive', due to a misplaced vertebra)
